<Verbatim PAsource="" >A Texan millionaire </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >was last night jailed for </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >85 years </Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >after being convicted of a high speed drink-drive boat crash off Florida which claimed the life of a British yacht captain and his five passengers. 
</New>

<Verbatim PAsource="" >Simon Prankerd, 32, </Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >from Truro, Cornwall, </New>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >was skippering </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >the </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >Bill It off Fort Lauderdale, </Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >when Stanley Cameron, 58, drove into him in his boat, Merrymaker. 

Cameron was found to be almost three times over the legal drink drive limit in November 1997. 

The circuit court heard Cameron had been driving at speeds of up to 60mph in a 20mph zone.


